<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; My expertise is in the crafty ways of the Thief.  There is no other job more interesting then THF because the job itself forces you to adapt to different stuations.  The THF functions differently depending on the party setup, mobs your fighting, areas your pulling from, and skillchains your closing, making every xp party a new and different experience.  The THF also seems to be the dominant force in the party in many situations, as doing a THF's job to its fullest requires us to have the main tank, trick buddy, skillchain partners, Sneak/Deodorizer (for SATA + Hide, if needed), and magic bursters under our thumb at all times.   Also, we are some of the best soloers in the game (other than Beastmaster, duh) with the right Marksmanship skills we can take out mobs that are Even Match or lower and camp NMs at lower levels than most other jobs would be able to.  Other perks of course are the farming and NM camping benefits given by TH1 and TH2, and the ability to pick our own chests and coffers without paying some greedy schmuck to get us a key (careful though, I died by a mimic in Monastic Cavern yesterday &gt;.&lt;). <br /> <br />  To wrap it all up, I like THF because it is the jack-of-all-trades job in the game that has the ability to play several different roles when the need arrives.  To me, and most other THF, there is no job as fun or as satisfying as THF, simply because the job keeps ya on your toes at all times. <br /> <br />edit: spelling. duh. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 31 14:28:42 2005 by KainRostecello</span></i></p>
