<p>This is an interesting question... I play 3 different jobs, I'll explain each: <br /> <br />Ranger - My main.&nbsp;&nbsp;At first, I just liked the idead of dishing out huge damage, but really... before 55, rangers aren't -that- much better than any other well equipped DD.  Now that I've toyed with it for a while, I like controlling the xp chains, knowing that if we do 2 crabs, a pug, 2 more crabs, and finish with a pug, we can get chain#5 for 360.  I'm constantly trying to optimize our chains. <br /> <br />A lot of rangers are only interested in blasting up big numbers.  I know damn well that I can sidewinder for 1000dmg on a crawler, but maybe if I save that for 500dmg on the next crab we'll get a better chain, hunh? <br /> <br />Ninja - My sub.  I used to hate tanking, but levelling War to 18 and Nin to 32 have given me much better appreciation for the hate thresholds that RNG &amp; BLM have to be so careful of in any party. <br /> <br />Thief - My latest toy.  Oh my god this job is fun to play... First SA+Fast Blade, then pull &amp; SATA, now I've just learned SATAVB... so much fun, and each fight is a bit different.  I'm also learning the &quot;joys&quot; of explaining sata to newer players /sigh.</p>
