<p>I particularly liked Kain's explanation of why he loved THF.&nbsp;&nbsp;I must also say, that Kain is probably the most skilled THF that I've had the pleasure of partying with, and I look forward to many nights of destruction with him.  That being said, I have two loves, as far as jobs go in XI. <br /> <br />White Mage.  I enjoy being the lifeblood of parties, I like the fact that when the SAM is afk, we can pull T and VTs, but when I'm afk, the party is on hold.  With that being said, I try to afk as little as possible and work those afk times into the full rests, after long chains.  I just feel, that WHM is a fun job, and it's involving, I often hear of WARs or MNKs that have afk'd during a battle, just auto-attack, and they go grab another beer.  If I would do that, I'd come back to 5 very angry dead bodies.  I enjoy the thrill of the fight, from a far perspective.  I don't even know what your in-game face looks like most of the time, but you better believe I can tell you what you max hitpoints are, and exactly when you take a hit, and what cure you're going to need.  I can also tell you when your haste is going to wear, and when Regen needs to be put back up.  I couldn't, for the life of me, tell you how much damage you're doing to the mob, or how close to dead it is, unless I'm preparing for my own little MB.  I particularly love a close battle once in a while.  As a tank, you get concerned when your HP is low.  That concerns me even more, be sure of that.  But when everyone's health is in the red, I worry about you all, at the same time.  I enjoy throwing out the heavy cures, and, in one quick thought, deciding who's getting a cure, and who will have to wait.  And I must say, I think I do a good job, as it's rare for me to lose someone in my party, unless I've either died first, or he/she got hit for an insane amount of damage.  <br /> <br />I enjoy raising people, I enjoy the thanks I get, for randomly Protecting anyone that I come in contact with that needs it.  I enjoy powerleveling parties, or helping someone out when a solo battle with a mob has gone wrong.  I enjoy being asked to sneak/invis someone through the last part of the PLD quest.   <br /> <br />WHM is just a job that I thoroughly enjoy... End of story. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />Bard. The ultimate support role.  Bard/White Mage.  I enjoy helping out the WHM, as I'll forever be a WHM at heart.  I enjoy coming into a party as BRD and seeing &quot;OMG We got a Bard! I love you&quot;  That always puts a smile on a minstrel's face.  I love being Lv. 25 and using that scroll of Ballad.  I love even more the joy from the mages, upon receiving Ballad, as I know exactly how great it is to have it on you.  And, to be honest, I think BRD's look the coolest, although I don't particularly like their AF, if what I've seen is, in fact, AF.  Nothing beats a lil taru running back and forth, with musical notes flowing serenely off his body and some effect wrapping party members up.  I also enjoy being able to get that Lullaby off, just at the right moment.  As of now, I'm a WHM, but only because I have a static.  Upon reaching 75, which I will, I'll begin the journey of getting Bard to 75, as on my old server, I never managed to get it past the mid-30s. <br /> <br />Sorry for the long-winded post, but I truly do love my jobs ^^</p>
