		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=332901"><span id="Scholar">Strangeone</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />528 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.67]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Strangeone&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Redmage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Why? probably because it's one of the most complicated jobs to do well.  What can I say, I like a challenge.  Now as far as what I'll do when (if ever) I hit 75?  Probably bring up one of my subs for HNMLS work as I've heard of an over supply of RDM at that level.  I'll probably use RDM as my special uses/Dynamis job and work something else like Ranger up for things like HNMLS and BCNM's.  Notice the long term plan.  You realy need to have long term plans in this game. <br /> <br />I've been playing for over a year and 3 months now.  I have come to realize that this game is very long term.  You also have to realize that this game will provide quite a bit of fustration - after all you are dealing with other humans behind the characters.  And let's face it a lot of our server could politely be described as ... Sociologicaly challenged ... <br /> <br />The real key to having fun in this game is to setup a lot of different short and long term objectives.  Some of these objectives should be acheivable solo and some should need party/ls/alliance to achieve. <br /> <br />The reson for this multiplicity of objectives is that if you pursue one thing above all other ins this game it's a recipe for fustration.  If you have a list of 10 things you want to do short term and the one you are trying to put toghether falls thru, well you have 9 other backup plans to work on.  This is what allows the intelligent gamer to do away with fustration.  You realize that all these other gamers are not here for your sole enjoyment of the game and they won't be at your beck and call at all hours of the day and night.  So the promy run isn't going to work out? time to go farm some clusters. <br /> <br />As a help to others, here is my list of short and long term objectives: <br /> <br /><b>Short Term</b> <br /> <br />Party/ls/alliance based: <br />Windy Mission 8-1 finished (getting tired of that doll). <br />ZM4 finished. <br />PM 2-5 (promisses to be a bad one). <br />any of the PROMY ENM's. <br /> <br />Small team/solo (THF anyone?): <br />Get map to Quicksand Caves. <br />Get map to Temple of Unpronouncable. <br />Get Bee Larvae to be able to get Hornetneedle. <br /> <br />Solo based: <br />Get cloth crafting to 60 <br />opporunisticaly work on Smithing, Goldsmithing, Leathercraft, Cooking and Alchemy. <br />Get to the top of The Tor in Attowha Chasm. <br />Skillup Dagger, Club and Archery till they are capped. <br />Get Bastok Fame up so I can at least flag last 2 avatar quests. <br /> <br /><b>Long Term</b> <br /> <br />Party/ls/alliance based: <br />Get in an HNMLS <br />Get in a Dynamis LS <br />Get all the avatars (including Fenrir) <br />Get Rank 10 <br />Get to Sky <br />Get to the point where I can do all the ENM's <br />Get a good freeflow team together for use in BCNM's (I've got 280 odd seals but I want to make sure the team is good before doing the higher level ones) <br />Get map of Pso'xja and &quot;finish&quot; that. <br /> <br />Solo/Team: <br />Get all the elemental summons. <br />Get all the promy maps. <br />Get all the dungeon maps. <br />Get enhancing sword. <br />Get an entire Duelists set. <br />Get an entire Blood/Crimson set. <br />Get all jobs to at least level 37 <br />Get 2 jobs to level 75 (min) <br />Cap all usable skills for RDM <br /> <br />Solo: <br />Get all crafts to 60 and pick one to go to 100 (except fishing). <br />Gett all the tele-scrolls. <br /> <br />With all of that to do, I never get fustrated when something doesn't work out or peeters out half way thru.  I always have about 8 different things I could be doing.  A lot of the fustration I have noticed is from people that don't have a list of things they could be doing.  Always setup multiple objectives.</p>
